            <li style="margin-bottom:30px">Information that has been given to you without your permission. Your personal information may be transferred to or received by us without our permission. In such situations, we’ll assess whether we have the legal authority to keep the information. Otherwise, if you provide us with the personal data of others (for example, a person to call in an emergency, professional referees), we will ask you to confirm that you have acquired their consent before giving us their information.</li>
