        <p><b>WHY</b> – We use your data to pursue our legitimate interests as an educational institution, employer, and/or contracting party, including a range of administrative, research, historical, and statistical purposes, to the degree authorized or required by law.</p>
        <p>We believe that processing your data for these reasons is essential for us to fulfill our contractual commitments to you, to comply with a legal duty, to safeguard your critically important interests, such as your life and health, and to carry out public-interest responsibilities (e.g., public order, public safety, etc.), or in the pursuit of the University’s or a third party’s legitimate interest. We recognize that the DPA sets more stringent regulations for the handling of sensitive personal information and privileged information, and we are completely committed to following them.</p>
        <p>If we need your permission for a specific use of your data, we will ask for it when the time comes.</p>
        <p style="margin-bottom:50px">Please be aware that we will not use your data for any automated decision-making without your permission.</p>
        
        <p style="margin-bottom:60px"><b>HOW</b> – Your personal information is securely kept and sent in a variety of paper and electronic formats, including databases, shared across the University’s many departments or offices. Access to your data is restricted to university employees who have a legitimate interest in them in order to fulfill their contractual obligations. Rest assured that our use of your data will be limited to what is necessary to achieve the purpose for which they were collected, and/or only when permitted by law.</p>
    
